00078 static void dumpHelp(void){
00079   int i, rc;
00080   char *name, *sname, *description;
00081   int id;
00082   printf("Build Ensemble: a tool for generating a dataset that contains multiple tree representations of\n"
00083          "  the input mesh.\n"
00084       "\n"
00085       "Usage: build_ensemble [options]\n"
00086          "  -n number_trees                 How many unique trees to generate\n"
00087          "  -w whittle_type                 Whittle algorithm to use\n");
00088 
00089   for(i=0; (rc=getNextWhittleAlgorithmDescription(i,&name, &sname, &id, &description)); i++){
00090     printf("        %s : %23s - %s\n", sname, name, description);
00091   }
00092 
00093 
00094   printf("\n"
00095       "  -p whittle_percent              percentage of tree to leave behind (1-99)\n"
00096          "  -m mesh_name[step]              (can be appended with displacement step, like block_1[2])\n"
00097          "  -d displacement_variable_name   (does combinding on _x,_y,_z and defaults to 'displacement')\n"
00098          "  -v                              (display warning messages)\n"
00099          "  -V                              (display log messages)\n"
00100          "  -h                              (this help screen)\n"
00101          "  -I ##                           Use the following built-in input files:\n");
00102   for(i=0; defaults[i].file; i++)
00103     printf("     %d : %s\n", i, defaults[i].info);
00104 
00105   exit(0);
00106 }

00108 static int getIndexAndTruncateName(char *name){
00109   char *c;
00110   c=name;
00111   while(*c!='\0') {
00112     if(*c=='['){
00113       *c='\0';
00114       c++;
00115       return atoi(c);
00116     }
00117     c++;
00118   }
00119   return -1; //No index, assume initial geometry
00120 }

00122 static void checkArgs(int argc, char **argv,
00123                 FC_VerbosityLevel   *verbose_level,
00124                 char                **file_name_i,
00125                 char                **file_name_o,
00126                 char                **mesh_name,
00127                 char                **disp_name,
00128                 int                  *step1,
00129                 int                  *num_trees,
00130                 whittleAlgorithm_t   *whittle_type,
00131                 int                  *percent){
00132   
00133   int ich;
00134   int i,id;
00135  
00136 
00137   if(argc<2) dumpHelp();
00138 
00139   *file_name_i = *file_name_o = *mesh_name = *disp_name = NULL;
00140   *whittle_type = FC_WA_UNKNOWN;
00141   *percent = 50;
00142   *step1 = -1; //Initial location
00143   *num_trees = 1;
00144 
00145   while( (ich = getopt(argc, argv, "i:o:m:d:p:w:n:I:vVh")) != EOF){
00146     switch(ich){
00147     case 'i':  *file_name_i   = strdup(optarg); break;
00148     case 'o':  *file_name_o   = strdup(optarg); break;
00149     case 'm':  *mesh_name     = strdup(optarg); break;
00150     case 'd':  *disp_name     = strdup(optarg); break;
00151     case 'p':  *percent       = atoi(optarg);   break;
00152     case 'w':  *whittle_type  = convertStringToWhittleAlg(optarg); break;
00153     case 'n':  *num_trees     = atoi(optarg); break;
00154     case 'v':  *verbose_level = FC_WARNING_MESSAGES; break;
00155     case 'V':  *verbose_level = FC_LOG_MESSAGES;     break;
00156   
00157     
00158     
00159     
00160     case 'I':
00161       id = atoi(optarg);
00162       for(i=0; (i<id) && (defaults[i].file); i++);
00163       if((id<0)||(!defaults[i].file)){
00164      printf("Default id (%d) out of range?\n", id);
00165      dumpHelp();
00166      exit(0);
00167       }
00168       *file_name_i         = strdup(defaults[i].file);
00169       *mesh_name         = strdup(defaults[i].mesh);
00170       *disp_name = (defaults[i].displacement) ? defaults[i].displacement : NULL;
00171       printf("Running with default %d: %s\n", i, defaults[i].info);
00172       break;
00173     
00174     case 'h': 
00175     default: 
00176       dumpHelp(); break;
00177     }
00178   }
00179 
00180   //Grab the input filename or die
00181   if(optind<argc)
00182     *file_name_i = strdup(argv[optind++]);
00183 
00184 
00185   if(*num_trees<1){
00186     printf("Need to make at least one tree");
00187     dumpHelp();
00188   }
00189 
00190 
00191   if((!*file_name_i)||(!*mesh_name)){
00192     printf("Error: not all required input fields defined\n");
00193     dumpHelp();
00194   }
00195 
00196   //See if there's a timestep index in mesh names (ie, block_1[3])
00197   *step1 = getIndexAndTruncateName(*mesh_name);
00198 
00199   //Assign the default displacement name
00200   if((*step1>=0)&&(!*disp_name)) *disp_name = strdup("displacement");
00201 
00202   
00203 
00204   return;
00205 }

00208 static FC_ReturnCode getMeshByNameOrDie(FC_Dataset ds, char *mesh_name, FC_Mesh *m){
00209 
00210   FC_ReturnCode rc;
00211   FC_Mesh *meshes;
00212   int numMeshes;
00213 
00214   rc = fc_getMeshByName(ds, mesh_name, &numMeshes, &meshes);
00215   fc_exitIfError(rc);
00216   
00217   if(numMeshes!=1)
00218     emsg("Found %d meshes named %s", numMeshes, mesh_name);
00219 
00220   *m = meshes[0];
00221   FREE(meshes);
00222   return FC_SUCCESS;

00236 int main(int argc, char **argv){
00237 
00238   FC_ReturnCode rc;
00239   FC_VerbosityLevel verbose_level = FC_WARNING_MESSAGES;
00240   
00241   char *file_name_i, *file_name_o;
00242   char *mesh_name, *disp_name;
00243   whittleAlgorithm_t wa=FC_WA_UNKNOWN;
00244   double wa_fraction;
00245 
00246   whittleAlgorithm_t *whittle_algs;
00247   double *whittle_fracs;
00248 
00249   int same_center=0;
00250   int same_whittle_alg=1;
00251   int same_whittle_frac=0;

00253   FC_Dataset ds1;
00254   FC_Dataset ds_skel;
00255   FC_Mesh    m1;
00256   int        step1;
00257 
00258   spanning_tree_t *tree1=NULL, *tree2=NULL;
00259  
00260   
00261   int *centers;
00262   char *mname;
00263   int num_trees=1;
00264   int num_elem;
00265   int percent;
00266   int i,j;
00267 
00268 
00269   //Look at args user gave us
00270   checkArgs(argc, argv, 
00271          &verbose_level, 
00272          &file_name_i, &file_name_o,
00273          &mesh_name, &disp_name, &step1,
00274          &num_trees,
00275          &wa, &percent);
00276 
00277  //Pass back info to user
00278   info("build_ensemble is running with args\n"
00279        "\tInput File   = '%s'\n"
00280        "\tOutput File  = '%s'\n"
00281        "\tMesh Name    = '%s'\n"
00282        "\tDisplacement = '%s'\n"
00283        "\tAlgorithm    = '%s'\n"
00284        "\tPercent      =  %d%%'",
00285        file_name_i,
00286        file_name_o,
00287        mesh_name,
00288        disp_name,
00289        getWhittleAlgorithmName(wa),
00290        percent);  
00291 
00292   wa_fraction = ((double)percent)/100.0;
00293 
00294   rc = fc_setLibraryVerbosity(verbose_level);         fc_exitIfError(rc);
00295   rc = fc_initLibrary();                              fc_exitIfError(rc);
00296 
00297   //Load the first mesh
00298   rc = fc_loadDataset(file_name_i, &ds1);             fc_exitIfError(rc);
00299   rc = getMeshByNameOrDie(ds1, mesh_name, &m1);      fc_exitIfError(rc);
00300 
00301 
00302   rc = fc_getMeshNumElement(m1, &num_elem);           fc_exitIfError(rc);
00303   printf("%d\n",num_trees);
00304 
00305   if(num_elem<num_trees) num_trees=num_elem; //Limit
00306 
00307 
00308   printf("Making %d spanning trees\n",num_trees);
00309 
00310   rc = fc_createDataset("skelozos", &ds_skel);        fc_exitIfError(rc);
00311 
00312   mname = (char *)mallocOrDie( (strlen("tree_")+5) * 2);
00313   centers = (int *)mallocOrDie(num_trees*sizeof(int));
00314   whittle_algs   = (whittleAlgorithm_t *)mallocOrDie(num_trees*sizeof(whittleAlgorithm_t));
00315   whittle_fracs  = (double *)mallocOrDie(num_trees*sizeof(double));
00316 
00317 
00318   //Figure out where centers should be
00319   if(same_center){
00320     //All have same center
00321     centers[0] = (int) ((double)(num_elem-1)) * (rand()/(RAND_MAX+1.0));
00322     for(i=1; i<num_trees-1; i++)
00323       centers[i] = centers[0];
00324   } else {
00325     //Different center for each node
00326     for(i=0; i<num_trees; i++){
00327       //Generate a new random center until we get a unique val
00328       do{
00329      centers[i] = (int) ((double)(num_elem-1)) * (rand()/(RAND_MAX+1.0));
00330      for(j=0; (j<i) && (centers[i]!=centers[j]) ; j++);
00331       } while (j<i);
00332     }
00333   }
00334 
00335   //Figure out which algorithm to use on each tree
00336   if(same_whittle_alg){
00337     for(i=0; i<num_trees; i++)
00338       whittle_algs[i] = wa;
00339   } else {
00340     for(i=0; i<num_trees; i++){
00341       switch(i%4){
00342       case 0: whittle_algs[i] = FC_WA_OCTANTS; break;
00343       case 1: whittle_algs[i] = FC_WA_MIN_DESCENDANTS; break;
00344       case 2: whittle_algs[i] = FC_WA_MIN_SEGMENT_LENGTHS; break;
00345       case 3: whittle_algs[i] = FC_WA_MIN_ANGLE_CHANGE; break;
00346       default:
00347      emsg("Bad case?");
00348       }
00349     }
00350   }
00351 
00352 
00353   //Figure out percentage we should use
00354   if(same_whittle_frac){
00355     for(i=0; i<num_trees; i++)
00356       whittle_fracs[i] = wa_fraction;
00357   } else {
00358     for(i=0; i<num_trees; i++)
00359       whittle_fracs[i] = 0.9 - (0.8/(double)num_trees)*((double)i);
00360   }
00361     
00362 
00363 
00364 
00365   for(i=0; i<num_trees; i++){
00366     //Build new tree
00367     printf("Building (%d/%d): center=%d Whittle=%.2lf WA=%s\n",
00368         i, num_trees, centers[i], whittle_fracs[i], convertWhittleAlgToString(whittle_algs[i])); 
00369     rc = fc_makeSpanningTree(m1, centers[i], &tree1); fc_exitIfError(rc);
00370 
00371     if(whittle_algs[i]!=FC_WA_UNKNOWN){
00372 
00373       rc = whittleSkeleton(tree1, whittle_algs[i], whittle_fracs[i], &tree2); fc_exitIfError(rc);
00374 
00375       FREE(tree1->nodes);
00376       FREE(tree1);
00377       tree1 = tree2;
00378       tree2 = NULL;
00379     }
00380 
00381 
00382 
00383     sprintf(mname, "tree_%.4d", centers[i]);
00384     printf("Writing mesh '%s'\n", mname);
00385     rc = fc_convertTreeToMesh(ds_skel, *tree1, mname, disp_name , NULL);
00386 
00387   }
00388   
00389   printf("Trying to write\n");
00390   rc = fc_writeDataset(ds_skel, file_name_o, FC_FT_EXODUS);
00391   fc_exitIfError(rc);
00392 
00393 
00394   printf("Done\n"); 
00395   FREE(whittle_fracs);
00396   FREE(whittle_algs);
00397   FREE(centers);
00398 
00399 
00400   return 0;
00401 }
